# Python cache and test artifacts
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*$py.class
.pytest_cache/
.mypy_cache/
.ruff_cache/

# Virtual environments
.venv/
venv/
env/

# IDE and OS files
# Keep local desktop-tool clutter out of the repo by default.
# Keep workflow/debug artifacts tracked unless we explicitly decide they are local-only.
.vscode/
.idea/
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
Desktop.ini

# Logs
*.log

# Local prompt/reference images and temporary visual inputs; keep prompt compression/test screenshots out.
测试图/
ComfyUI_*.png
ComfyUI_*.jpg
ComfyUI_*.jpeg
ComfyUI_*.webp
ComfyUI_*.gif
ComfyUI_*.bmp

# Local release packaging scratch artifacts; tracked release installers remain under Game content extraction/release.
.release-assets/

# Prompt polishing follows tracked markdown files; expression expansion/regression uses tracked tests and workflow scripts.
# Rule-doc sync files such as agents.md, README.md and 组图 23.md stay tracked; List 2 dedupe/high-visibility guidance belongs in docs, not ignore rules.
# Prompt/spec compression review edits stay tracked; no markdown ignore rules here.
# Brainstorm/spec/execution workflow outputs are kept trackable when they document accepted project direction, including blind-box itemization patch specs.
# Expression history tests create temp folders only on failed/interrupted runs.
Game content extraction/_tmp_history_test_*/
Game content extraction/_tmp_history_verify_*/

# Desktop app build/release artifacts are intentionally tracked in this repo.
# Release/update debugging records stay tracked when they document public release behavior.
# Keep ignore changes scoped to untracked local clutter only.
# Spec/product-brief session outputs remain tracked when they record accepted requirements and glossary decisions.
